CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 21, 1944, p. 13, reads: "BILLY ECKSTINE, the famed orchestra leader, seems intrigued at whatever that is Lena is showing him at the reception given in her honor at the nationally known Loendi Club last Wednesday night. - Staff Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Billy Eckstine and Lena Horne standing behind cake, with Miriam Sharpe Fountain in background on left, in Loendi Club, for reception in honor of Horne
